   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the screws and the top and bottom front plates from
the transformer cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Transformer Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_50kwditransf_preparetopentry_removefrontplates_w120mm_0000166573.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the top plate in the transformer cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Transformer Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_50kwditransf_preparetopentry_removetopplate_w120mm_0000166572.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Drill holes and install conduits for bypass cables in the
top plate. Conduits are not provided.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <hazardstatement type="danger">
                  <messagepanel>
                     <typeofhazard>Hazard of electric shock, explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
                     <howtoavoid>Do not drill or cut holes for cables or conduits with
the top plate installed and do not drill or cut holes in close proximity
to the UPS.</howtoavoid>
                  </messagepanel>
               </hazardstatement>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reinstall the top plate in the transformer cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Transformer Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_50kwditransf_preparetopentry_reinstalltopplate_w120mm_0000166571.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
      </ol>
